The Olivier Awards for theatre were handed out in London on Sunday, with the musical "Cabaret" and play "Life of Pi" the productions scooping the most prizes. Below is a list of winners in the key categories. 1. BEST NEW PLAY "Life Of Pi" 2. BEST NEW MUSICAL "Back To The Future - The Musical" 3. BEST MUSICAL REVIVAL "Cabaret" 4. BEST REVIVAL "Constellations" 5. BEST ENTERTAINMENT OR COMEDY PLAY "Pride And Prejudice* (*Sort Of)" 6. BEST ACTRESS Sheila Atim, "Constellations" 7. BEST ACTOR Hiran Abeysekera, "Life Of Pi" 8. BEST ACTOR IN A MUSICAL Eddie Redmayne, "Cabaret" 9. BEST ACTRESS IN A MUSICAL Jessie Buckley, "Cabaret" 10. BEST ACTOR IN A SUPPORTING ROLE Seven actors who play the Tiger, "Life Of Pi" 11. BEST ACTRESS IN A SUPPORTING ROLE Liz Carr, "The Normal Heart" 12. BEST ACTRESS IN A SUPPORTING ROLE IN A MUSICAL Liza Sadovy, "Cabaret" 13. BEST ACTOR IN A SUPPORTING ROLE IN A MUSICAL Elliot Levey, "Cabaret" 14. BEST ORIGINAL SCORE OR NEW ORCHESTRATIONS Orchestrator Simon Hale, "Get Up, Stand Up! The Bob Marley Musical" 15. BEST DIRECTOR Rebecca Frecknall, "Cabaret"